189
00:09:44,641 --> 00:09:47,082
It was to help ordinary people, right?

190
00:09:47,282 --> 00:09:48,761
To help those without good jobs,

191
00:09:48,802 --> 00:09:50,162
so they could gain knowledge

192
00:09:50,202 --> 00:09:51,682
and master a skill.

193
00:09:51,881 --> 00:09:54,241
That's how they could improve
their lives. Correct?

194
00:09:54,562 --> 00:09:55,841
That's why we all supported you.

195
00:09:55,881 --> 00:09:57,656
Both Lin and I were on your side.

196
00:09:57,656 --> 00:09:58,648
Now look at this mess.

197
00:09:59,448 --> 00:10:00,402
A sensation?

198
00:10:00,641 --> 00:10:02,082
What are they teaching?

199
00:10:02,481 --> 00:10:03,042
His teachings

200
00:10:03,641 --> 00:10:05,922
prioritize money,
and that is problematic.

201
00:10:06,121 --> 00:10:07,082
You're narrow-minded.

202
00:10:07,322 --> 00:10:08,042
I'm narrow-minded?

203
00:10:08,241 --> 00:10:09,841
You need this night school most.

204
00:10:10,082 --> 00:10:11,601
I'll definitely sign you up, okay?

205
00:10:11,601 --> 00:10:12,282
Leave it to me.

206
00:10:12,521 --> 00:10:13,361
Xie Chunlai,

207
00:10:13,442 --> 00:10:14,442
these ten points...

208
00:10:14,481 --> 00:10:16,001
No. We're done talking.

209
00:10:16,241 --> 00:10:18,008
I'm the acting mayor.

210
00:10:18,008 --> 00:10:19,481
I'll take all the responsibility.

211
00:10:19,641 --> 00:10:21,202
- Even if you're the mayor...
- Mr. Tan.

212
00:10:21,202 --> 00:10:22,962
- If you mess up...
- The night school issue

213
00:10:23,322 --> 00:10:24,322
