245
00:11:34,881 --> 00:11:36,202
Alien technology?

246
00:11:36,562 --> 00:11:38,082
Related to alien technology?

247
00:11:38,562 --> 00:11:39,442
Alien technology?

248
00:11:40,721 --> 00:11:41,761
Professor He,

249
00:11:42,282 --> 00:11:44,481
could you tell us
about alien technology today?

250
00:11:44,641 --> 00:11:45,322
Alien technology.

251
00:11:45,402 --> 00:11:46,761
- Yeah.
- What does that mean?

252
00:11:47,082 --> 00:11:48,641
What does 'alien technology' mean?

253
00:11:50,322 --> 00:11:51,042
Jie.

254
00:11:53,042 --> 00:11:54,121
- Xie.
- Xie.

255
00:11:54,802 --> 00:11:55,361
Xie.

256
00:11:55,682 --> 00:11:56,442
No.

257
00:11:57,721 --> 00:11:58,442
It's Xie.

258
00:11:59,082 --> 00:11:59,682
Well,

259
00:12:00,361 --> 00:12:01,361
it's not J-I-E.

260
00:12:01,601 --> 00:12:02,442
It's X-I-E.

261
00:12:05,322 --> 00:12:07,721
Professor He
mentioned alien technology earlier.

262
00:12:08,521 --> 00:12:09,162
Well,

263
00:12:09,721 --> 00:12:10,521
Mr. Xie,

264
00:12:11,001 --> 00:12:13,442
as the saying goes well,

265
00:12:13,881 --> 00:12:15,042
cosmic secrets stay hidden.

266
00:12:15,962 --> 00:12:18,841
It seems inconvenient for me to speak

267
00:12:19,922 --> 00:12:21,001
about these things here.

268
00:12:22,121 --> 00:12:22,721
Right.

269
00:12:23,481 --> 00:12:25,464
Professor He's visit here
wasn't easy to arrange.

270
00:12:26,641 --> 00:12:27,562
Professor He, look.

271
00:12:27,802 --> 00:12:29,282
Under this stage and outside

272
00:12:29,601 --> 00:12:34,182
are all pairs of eyes
eager to devour knowledge, right?

273
00:12:34,282 --> 00:12:36,162
If you don't share something, I'm afraid

274
00:12:36,841 --> 00:12:37,802
you can't leave.

275
00:12:38,402 --> 00:12:39,721
Tell us a bit, Professor He.

276
00:12:39,761 --> 00:12:40,601
Tell us a bit.

277
00:12:40,601 --> 00:12:41,241
